A '''deed of gift''' is a signed [[Legal instrument|legal document]] that voluntarily and without [[Financial compensation|recompense]] transfers [[Ownership|ownership]] of [[real property|real]], [[personal property|personal]], or [[intellectual property]] – such as a [[Gift|gift]] of materials – from one person or institution to another. It should include any possible conditions specifying access, use, preservation, etc. of the gift, although these are generally discouraged by recipient institutions.

