{{Infobox language family |name=Mangbetu–Asoa |altname=Mangbetu |region=[[Democratic Republic of Congo]] |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic]] |fam3=Eastern |child1=[[Mangbetu language|Mangbetu]] |child2=[[Lombi language (DRC)|Lombi]] |child3=[[Asoa language|Asoa]] |glotto=mang1393 |glottorefname=Mangbetu–Asua }}
The '''Mangbetu–Asoa''' or '''Mangbetu''' languages of the [[Central Sudanic languages|Central Sudanic language family]] are a cluster of closely related languages spoken in the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]].
The languages are [[Mangbetu language|Mangbetu]], spoken by perhaps a million people, and the smaller [[Lombi language (DRC)|Lombi]] and [[Asoa language|Asoa]]. Blench (2000) considers Lombi to be part of the Mangbetu dialect continuum. Asoa is spoken by [[Pygmy languages|Pygmies]].
