{{Infobox writer | name = N. Pankaja | image = | image_size = | caption = | native_name = ನುಗ್ಗೇಹಳ್ಳಿ ಪಂಕಜ | native_name_lang = Kannada | pseudonym = Nuggehalli Pankaja | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1929|6|2|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Bangalore]], [[Mysore State]], [[British India]] | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | occupation = | language = [[Kannada language|Kannada]], [[English language|English]] | nationality = Indian | ethnicity = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = | period = | genre = <!-- or: | genres = --> | subject = <!-- or: | subjects = --> | movement = | notableworks = <!-- or: | notablework = --> | spouse = <!-- or: | spouses = --> | partner = <!-- or: | partners = --> | children = | relatives = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | years_active = | module = | website = | portaldisp = <!-- "on", "yes", "true", etc; or omit --> }}
'''Nuggehalli Pankaja''' (born 2 June 1929) is an Indian writer and poet in the [[Kannada language|Kannada]] and [[English language]]s. She is considered one the notable writers in the Kannada language.<ref>{{cite web |title= Documentary films on 15 Kannada women writers |url= http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-karnataka/documentary-films-on-15-kannada-women-writers/article6115932.ece |publisher= ''The Hindu'' |date= 15 June 2014 |accessdate= 3 September 2014}}</ref> Her works include novels, short stories, and plays. She was conferred the Excellence in World Poetry Award by the International Academy for English Poetry.<ref>{{cite web |title= The Homepage of author Nuggehalli Pankaja |url= http://nuggehallipankaja.wordpress.com/ |accessdate= 3 September 2014}}</ref>
