'''Tupuri''' (or '''Toupouri''') is a language mostly spoken in the [[Mayo-Kebbi Est Region]] of southern [[Chad]] and in small parts of northern [[Cameroon]]. It is an [[Mbum languages|Mbum language]] spoken by the [[Tupuri people]] with approximately 300,000 speakers.

