{{Infobox person | name = Wilhelm Molly | image = Wilhelm Molly.jpg | alt = | caption = Wilhelm Molly | birth_name = | birth_date = 1838 | birth_place = Blasbach, [[Wetzlar]] | death_date = 1919 | death_place = [[Neutral Moresnet]] | nationality = | other_names = | occupation = Doctor | years_active = | known_for = [[Philately]] | notable_works = }}
'''Wilhelm Molly''' (1838–1919) was a doctor, [[Philately|philatelist]], [[Activism|activist]], and [[Esperantist]].<ref name="moresnet">{{cite web |title=Neutral-Moresnet History 1916–1919 |publisher=moresnet.nl |date= |url=http://www.moresnet.nl/english/geschiedenis_en.htm |accessdate=17 July 2016 |archiveurl=http://www.moresnet.nl/english/geschiedenis_en.htm |archivedate=25 November 2017}}</ref>
He was the chief medical doctor of the [[Vieille Montagne]] mining company.
As an avid philatelist, he tried to organize a local postal service with its own stamps. This enterprise was quickly thwarted by Belgian intervention.<ref name="moresnet"/><ref name="moresnet2">{{cite web |title=Stamps and postal history |publisher=moresnet.nl |date= |url=http://www.moresnet.nl/english/postverkeer_en.htm |accessdate=17 July 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160420132008/http://www.moresnet.nl/english/postverkeer_en.htm |archivedate=25 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Weber |first=Saine |title=Amikejo, Ort der Freundschaft |publisher=Deutschlandfunk |language=German |date=12 May 2008 |url=http://www.deutschlandfunk.de/amikejo-ort-der-freundschaft.1247.de.html?dram:article_id=190076 |accessdate=17 July 2016 }}</ref>
In 1908, Molly proposed to make Neutral Moresnet the world's first state with [[Esperanto]] as its official language, named ''Amikejo'' ({{abbr|lit.|literally}} ''Place of Friendship'').<ref name="moresnet"/>
